<br>
<br>
Loot that I have gotten since being in ADA on any ADA raid = zero. That was NOT the reason I/we left. If I (we) were a power gamer, I wouldnt go to our new guild. We are rebuilding, and we are doing it very fast. Thats not what we are about-uberness. Believe me we are about friends. Now truth be told, we hated some of the things that were going on and well it's in the past now. As for &quot;power-gamer,&quot; no. We are a group of friends, more tight now though. Loot isnt an issue to us btw, as you might think, injustices would be. Our loot rules are like a sentence long.  I think we won't put up with a lot of the things Ada did, cause we are different in personality.<br>
<br>
So we are different. Does this make us bad? Does it make us bad we want to actually know who all the ppl are in guildsay? Or many other things that differ from Ada, no. Does Ada seem like a bad group of folks, heck no.  <br>
<br>
This is a time for healing among friends not finger pointing. As to why we all left stealthfully, its actually because we didnt want to cause a bigger disturbance then we were about to, honestly. <br>
<br>
A lot of us tried to change things in ADA with posts and attempts to do more in the guild. These attempts were met with brutal opposition IMO. But even still, I don't have any ill will towards any AdA member btw. I call them friends, not foes. As for family, for me its with my new guild. But guildtag is indicative of family, some close friendships transcend guildtags--believe me.  <p><HTML>
